CatDescriptText: Related article published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 20, 1946, pg. 17, reads: "...Clyde O. Davis has done same [applied for marriage license] in order to make his Mrs. Julia Tyner of Atlantic City, N. J. ..."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, including groom, possibly Clyde Davis, wearing dark three piece suit, and nine women, including bride, possibly Julia Tyner Davis wearing dark suit, large corsage, and light colored crocheted blouse, and possibly Cleo Holloway Keith wearing floral blouse on left, posed behind wedding cake, in interior with diamond patterned curtains and striped wallpaper
